WEBVTT

00:06.464 --> 00:08.049
♪ (THEME MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

01:38.473 --> 01:39.766
♪ (MUSIC FADES) ♪

01:39.849 --> 01:41.893
(BEACHGOERS CHATTERING)

01:51.236 --> 01:55.490
(AMERICANS CHATTERING
INDISTINCTLY)

02:02.080 --> 02:03.998
AMERICAN 1: Anyways, I feel like
I can't even go back

02:04.082 --> 02:04.958
and get married to him.

02:05.041 --> 02:06.501
Pretend like
we never have to go back

02:06.584 --> 02:07.585
to America.

02:08.378 --> 02:09.671
AMERICAN 2: I think so.

02:09.754 --> 02:12.423
-I know, I think--
-Did you guys just get here?

02:12.507 --> 02:14.425
Yeah, we-- we just
in flew this morning.

02:14.509 --> 02:18.680
Oh, I'm so jealous.
We leave in a few hours.

02:18.763 --> 02:20.223
So, did you have a good time?

02:20.306 --> 02:24.143
We had the best time.
Have you guys been here before?

02:24.227 --> 02:25.228
No.

02:25.311 --> 02:28.356
The hotel's perfect,
and the staff is excellent.

02:29.274 --> 02:31.776
The food is amazing.

02:31.860 --> 02:34.821
-I've heard.
-And the wine. I mean...

02:34.904 --> 02:36.865
We are so excited.

02:36.948 --> 02:40.285
Italy's just so romantic.
Oh, you're gonna die.

02:40.368 --> 02:41.995
They're gonna have
to drag you out of here.

02:42.078 --> 02:43.872
-(CHUCKLES)
-Oh, I'm sure.

02:45.498 --> 02:48.418
Well, I'm gonna get
in the water one last time.

02:49.002 --> 02:50.253
But...

02:50.336 --> 02:52.130
you guys are gonna
have such an amazing trip.

02:52.213 --> 02:53.923
-Thank you. Nice to meet you.
-Thanks.

02:54.007 --> 02:55.425
-DAPHNE SULLIVAN: You too.
-Safe travels.

02:55.508 --> 02:57.176
-Thanks. Bye!
-AMERICANS: Bye!

02:59.429 --> 03:01.306
(WAVES CRASHING)

03:32.128 --> 03:33.630
Oh, what the fuck was that?

03:33.713 --> 03:35.256
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

03:36.633 --> 03:40.970
(GASPS) Holy fuck.
Oh, my fucking God.

03:41.596 --> 03:44.265
Holy fucking shit.

03:44.349 --> 03:50.146
Help! Help! Help! Help!

03:53.149 --> 03:54.692
Help! Help!

03:55.401 --> 03:56.736
Help!

03:56.819 --> 03:58.321
♪ (MUSIC FADES) ♪

03:58.404 --> 04:03.076
(REPORTERS CHATTERING
IN ITALIAN)

04:04.953 --> 04:06.120
Valentina.

04:06.204 --> 04:09.707
(IN ITALIAN)

04:20.259 --> 04:21.511
(INHALES)

04:36.317 --> 04:38.653
(SIREN WAILING)

04:38.736 --> 04:41.781
(HELICOPTER WHIRRING)

04:45.827 --> 04:49.288
-(COASTGUARD SPEAKING ITALIAN)
-(CROWD MURMURING NERVOUSLY)

04:49.372 --> 04:51.541
OFFICER: (IN ENGLISH)
You must stay behind there.

04:53.334 --> 04:55.795
-(HELICOPTER WHIRRING)
-(SIRENS WAILING)

04:55.878 --> 04:57.005
(INDISTINCT NERVOUS CHATTER)

04:57.088 --> 05:00.383
-(SEAGULL SQUAWKING)
-♪ (DRAMATIC MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

05:06.305 --> 05:07.849
♪ (MUSIC SWELLS, FADES) ♪

05:07.932 --> 05:13.062
♪ ("A FAR L'AMORE COMINCIA TU"
BY RAFFAELLA CARRÀ PLAYING) ♪

05:20.111 --> 05:26.826
♪ (SINGER SINGING IN ITALIAN) ♪

05:47.346 --> 05:52.894
♪ (SONG CONTINUES) ♪

06:12.246 --> 06:17.585
♪ (SONG CONTINUES) ♪

06:20.421 --> 06:21.964
♪ (SONG CONTINUES
OVER HEADPHONES) ♪

06:22.048 --> 06:23.466
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

06:23.549 --> 06:25.301
-Allora!
-(GASPS) Oh.

06:25.635 --> 06:26.552
Mia.

06:26.636 --> 06:27.929
♪ (SONG STOPS) ♪

06:29.222 --> 06:30.098
Huh?

06:35.353 --> 06:36.395
(BREATHES DEEPLY)

06:41.984 --> 06:44.403
(BOTH SAYING GOODBYE IN ITALIAN)

06:44.487 --> 06:45.488
-Sì!
-♪ (SONG RESUMES) ♪

06:45.571 --> 06:47.281
(CONVERSING IN ITALIAN)

06:47.365 --> 06:51.494
-♪ (SONG CONTINUES) ♪
-♪ (SINGER SINGING IN ITALIAN) ♪

06:58.251 --> 07:00.169
♪ (SONG CONTINUES) ♪

07:04.757 --> 07:06.843
-♪ (SONG CONCLUDES) ♪
-VALENTINA:

07:21.190 --> 07:23.442
(GUESTS CHATTERING)

07:30.616 --> 07:31.576
(SIGHS)

07:32.368 --> 07:35.830
-MIA:
-LUCIA:

07:44.005 --> 07:45.464
VALENTINA: Signori Di Grasso.

07:45.548 --> 07:47.592
(IN ENGLISH)
Welcome to the White Lotus.

07:47.675 --> 07:50.219
I am Valentina,
the resort manager.

07:50.303 --> 07:52.054
-BERT DI GRASSO: Ah.
-How was your boat ride?

07:52.138 --> 07:53.723
It was bellissimo.

07:53.806 --> 07:56.642
I mean, I'm impressed
that you are even here.

07:56.726 --> 07:57.852
Why are you impressed?

07:57.935 --> 07:59.854
VALENTINA: It's a long trip
from Los Angeles,

07:59.937 --> 08:02.190
and you are quite old, no?

08:02.273 --> 08:05.776
-Anyway, Isabella here
will take you up to the hotel...
-♪ (INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

08:05.860 --> 08:07.820
...and bring you
to your beautiful rooms.

08:07.904 --> 08:09.697
Can I offer you
a glass of Prosecco?

08:09.780 --> 08:12.783
Oh. Thank you, dear.
You're a sight for sore eyes.

08:12.867 --> 08:14.035
-(CHUCKLES)
-Thank you.

08:14.118 --> 08:15.036
-Cheers.
-ISABELLA: This way.

08:15.119 --> 08:16.037
-Thank you.
-You like it?

08:16.120 --> 08:17.538
DOMINIC DI GRASSO: Yeah. Thanks.

08:17.622 --> 08:18.664
Hello, darling.

08:19.207 --> 08:20.166
Oh.

08:20.249 --> 08:21.542
(IN ITALIAN)

08:21.626 --> 08:23.377
VALENTINA: (IN ENGLISH)
Hey. Welcome to Sicily.

08:23.461 --> 08:24.712
(IN ITALIAN)

08:25.880 --> 08:26.923
(GASPS)

08:27.006 --> 08:28.758
VALENTINA: (IN ENGLISH)
Mr. and Mrs. Sullivan.

08:28.841 --> 08:31.135
(IN ITALIAN)

08:31.219 --> 08:33.596
VALENTINA: (IN ENGLISH)
You must be
Mr. and Mrs. Spiller?

08:33.679 --> 08:34.931
(IN ITALIAN)

08:35.014 --> 08:36.515
VALENTINA: (IN ENGLISH)
How was your flight?

08:36.599 --> 08:37.892
-It was fine.
-Yeah.

08:37.975 --> 08:39.810
-But they did lose
Cameron's bag in Rome.
-(INHALES DEEPLY)

08:39.894 --> 08:44.232
Oh, never transfer through Rome.
Fiumicino always loses bags.

08:44.315 --> 08:45.316
BOTH: Oh.

08:45.399 --> 08:47.151
You should have
flown through Munich.

08:47.235 --> 08:48.903
(CHUCKLES)

08:48.986 --> 08:50.404
-Thanks for the tip.
-Yeah. Next time.

08:50.488 --> 08:51.739
-You're welcome.
-DAPHNE: Thank you.

08:51.822 --> 08:54.200
Please, some Italian Prosecco?

08:54.283 --> 08:56.327
-Let's toast, people.
-No, thanks.

08:56.410 --> 08:58.913
-I think I'll just wait.
-Harper-- You don't want one?

08:58.996 --> 09:00.581
No. I don't want one. (SIGHS)

09:00.665 --> 09:02.708
ETHAN SPILLER:
They wanna do a toast.
Can you hold the glass for me?

09:02.792 --> 09:04.168
HARPER SPILLER:
I haven't eaten in six hours.

09:04.252 --> 09:06.003
-I don't need any more drinks.
-Sorry. (CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)

09:06.629 --> 09:07.672
Just hold it.

09:09.131 --> 09:10.800
-Sorry. (CHUCKLES NERVOUSLY)
-DAPHNE: That's okay.

09:10.883 --> 09:12.802
-Cheers. We made it.
-Cheers.

09:12.885 --> 09:15.513
VALENTINA: Welcome
to the White Lotus in Sicily.

09:15.596 --> 09:16.681
Mm. Thank you.

09:16.764 --> 09:18.224
VALENTINA:
If your bag will ever arrive,

09:18.307 --> 09:20.268
-we'll let you know right way.
-Okay.

09:20.351 --> 09:21.644
If you believe in miracles.

09:21.727 --> 09:23.396
-(CHUCKLES) Okay, thank you.
-(DAPHNE CHUCKLES)

09:23.479 --> 09:26.524
You're welcome.
So, you don't like Prosecco?

09:26.607 --> 09:28.651
-No, no, it's fine. Thank you.
-Yeah.

09:31.153 --> 09:33.948
-Okay. Okay. Thank you.
-Okay, careful.

09:34.031 --> 09:37.285
TANYA MCQUOID:
Ah! Ah! (PANTS) Oh.

09:37.368 --> 09:38.619
VALENTINA: Mrs. McQuoid-Hunt!

09:38.703 --> 09:39.996
-TANYA: Ooh.
-(IN ITALIAN)

09:40.079 --> 09:41.956
VALENTINA: (IN ENGLISH) Welcome
to the White Lotus in Sicily.

09:42.039 --> 09:44.292
LUCIA: (IN ITALIAN)

09:44.375 --> 09:45.710
(IN ENGLISH) You guys
just really--

09:45.793 --> 09:47.878
just pull out all the stops.
You really do.

09:47.962 --> 09:50.172
Whenever I stay
at a White Lotus,

09:50.256 --> 09:53.217
I always have
a memorable time. Always.

09:53.301 --> 09:55.303
And you are
in our Blossom Circle.

09:55.386 --> 09:57.596
So, you are
very important to us.

09:57.680 --> 10:00.683
Mm. But I was a Petal,

10:00.766 --> 10:03.728
and I've worked
my way up to Blossom. Yeah.

10:04.937 --> 10:07.773
You know that your husband
is already here?

10:07.857 --> 10:09.442
Good. Because... (SCOFFS)

10:09.525 --> 10:11.402
...he hasn't been responding
to my texts.

10:11.902 --> 10:12.987
Shall we?

10:13.070 --> 10:15.698
Yeah, okay. Okay,
Portia, do you get service here?

10:15.781 --> 10:17.408
PORTIA: Yeah, I think
we both have full service.

10:17.491 --> 10:19.368
TANYA: Maybe we could take it
to AT&T or something.

10:19.452 --> 10:21.871
♪ ("BOCCA DI ROSA"
BY FABRIZIO DE ANDRÉ PLAYING) ♪

10:21.954 --> 10:25.207
♪ (SINGER SINGING IN ITALIAN) ♪

10:35.217 --> 10:37.762
♪ (SONG CONTINUES) ♪

11:00.743 --> 11:02.286
♪ (SONG CONCLUDES) ♪

11:02.370 --> 11:04.121
(GASPS, IN ENGLISH) Wow.

11:05.122 --> 11:06.540
This hotel is so cool.

11:06.624 --> 11:08.000
ROCCO: Well, originally,
it was a convent.

11:08.084 --> 11:09.710
Honey, check out this view.

11:09.794 --> 11:13.464
-Whoa. Is that a volcano?
-CAMERON SULLIVAN: Mount Etna.

11:13.547 --> 11:15.591
Hey, what is with these
head things?

11:15.674 --> 11:17.093
We keep seeing them everywhere.

11:17.176 --> 11:18.386
Testa di Moro.

11:18.469 --> 11:20.596
-ETHAN: Testa di Moro?
-ROCCO: Yeah. Well, the story is

11:20.679 --> 11:24.475
a Moor came here a long time ago
and seduced a local girl.

11:24.558 --> 11:27.520
But then she found out
that he had a wife

11:27.603 --> 11:29.063
and children back home.

11:29.146 --> 11:30.231
(CLICKS TONGUE, GROANS)

11:30.314 --> 11:33.025
So, because he lied to her,
she cut his head off.

11:33.109 --> 11:34.235
-ETHAN: Oh.
-Jesus.

11:34.318 --> 11:35.945
So if you put one
of those outside of your house,

11:36.028 --> 11:37.071
what are you saying?

11:37.154 --> 11:38.823
If you come into my house,
don't fuck my wife.

11:38.906 --> 11:40.032
-(LAUGHS)
-(CHUCKLES)

11:40.116 --> 11:41.367
DAPHNE: It's a warning
to husbands, babe.

11:41.450 --> 11:43.244
Screw around and you'll end up
buried in the garden.

11:43.327 --> 11:45.204
-Uh-oh.
-Oh, before I forget.

11:45.287 --> 11:46.914
I'll show you a special feature.

11:46.997 --> 11:48.749
-CAMERON: Cool.
-If I open this door,

11:48.833 --> 11:50.251
you can connect the two rooms.

11:50.334 --> 11:51.502
-Should I show you?
-Oh! Yeah, cool.

11:51.585 --> 11:53.337
No, no, that's okay.
I doubt we'll use that.

11:54.630 --> 11:56.966
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

11:57.049 --> 11:58.759
-(EXHALES DEEPLY)
-Okay.

12:00.094 --> 12:02.304
I mean, it's possible
at some point. I don't know.

12:02.388 --> 12:04.014
It's good to have
the option, yeah?

12:04.098 --> 12:05.141
-DAPHNE: Yeah.
-Yeah.

12:05.766 --> 12:06.809
ETHAN: You never know.

12:08.936 --> 12:10.896
-Guys, we did it!
-(GIGGLES) Yeah!

12:10.980 --> 12:11.939
Come on! We're finally here!

12:12.022 --> 12:13.357
We've been talking
about this forever.

12:13.441 --> 12:14.984
-This is awesome.
-DAPHNE: Oh! I'm so happy
we're here.

12:15.067 --> 12:16.777
-It's gonna be great.
-CAMERON: Yeah.

12:16.861 --> 12:17.820
Yeah, totally.

12:20.906 --> 12:22.158
-Let me show you your rooms.
-BOTH: Yeah!

12:22.241 --> 12:23.534
-ROCCO: Let's go.
-(HARPER CLEARS THROAT)

12:23.617 --> 12:24.994
-You go first.
-ETHAN: All right, guys.
See you later.

12:25.077 --> 12:27.204
-Yeah. See you.
-(DOOR OPENS)

12:27.288 --> 12:28.581
(SIGHS)

12:28.664 --> 12:30.541
-(DOOR CLOSES)
-(ETHAN BREATHES DEEPLY)

12:31.584 --> 12:32.585
What?

12:32.918 --> 12:34.170
(SCOFFS)

12:37.256 --> 12:39.258
BERT: Oh. I should tell you.

12:39.341 --> 12:41.510
Both my parents
were born in Sicily.

12:41.594 --> 12:42.720
-Oh.
-Yeah, they came

12:42.803 --> 12:45.848
to the States as children.
Yeah, so we are Sicilian,

12:45.931 --> 12:47.016
just like you.

12:47.099 --> 12:49.185
Although I'm not from Sicily.
I am from Milan.

12:49.268 --> 12:51.437
Oh, you do have more
of a Northern look.

12:51.520 --> 12:55.608
Beautiful hazel eyes.
Wonderful smile. (CHUCKLES)

12:55.691 --> 12:58.486
-(GIGGLES) You're very kind.
-BERT: You must be very popular.

12:58.569 --> 13:00.029
(CHUCKLES)

13:00.112 --> 13:02.364
-DOMINIC: All right, Dad.
-BERT: Ah.

13:02.448 --> 13:06.118
Anyway, we're here because
we're gonna visit the town

13:06.202 --> 13:07.620
-my grandmother's from.
-Oh!

13:07.703 --> 13:10.998
It's a little town,
uh, Testa dell'Acqua.

13:11.081 --> 13:12.750
Yeah, that sounds very special.

13:13.250 --> 13:14.418
(BERT FARTS)

13:19.048 --> 13:22.092
Hopefully, um,
we can find some people there

13:22.176 --> 13:23.719
who can speak English,
you know,

13:23.802 --> 13:25.888
maybe help us track down
some distant relatives.

13:25.971 --> 13:27.556
‘Cause we definitely
don't speak Italian.

13:27.640 --> 13:30.059
-(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)
-Oh, you should come, Isabella.

13:30.142 --> 13:33.145
You could be our translator.
We need you.

13:33.229 --> 13:34.438
-Dad.
-BERT: Hmm?

13:34.522 --> 13:36.357
Leave her alone.
We'll take it from here.

13:36.440 --> 13:37.775
Okay, thank you.

13:37.858 --> 13:39.610
Shall I show you how
to close the curtains?

13:39.693 --> 13:41.237
There's a button
over there on the--

13:41.320 --> 13:42.530
That's okay.
We'll figure it out.

13:42.613 --> 13:44.949
I'd like to know.
Where is this button, Isabella?

13:45.032 --> 13:47.993
Dad! I'm gonna help
you find it, okay?

13:48.077 --> 13:51.080
-Thank you very, very much.
-Thank you. Thank you very much.

13:51.163 --> 13:52.873
-Thank you.
-You're very lovely.

13:52.957 --> 13:53.874
Thank you.

13:53.958 --> 13:56.085
They are lucky
to have you working here.

13:56.168 --> 13:58.254
-(ISABELLA CHUCKLING)
-BERT: Be our translator--

13:58.337 --> 13:59.755
(DOOR SLAMMING SHUT)

13:59.838 --> 14:02.633
You slammed the door
in that poor girl's face!

14:02.716 --> 14:04.552
You were harassing her.

14:04.635 --> 14:07.888
-How? I was not.
-You kinda were. And farting.

14:09.056 --> 14:10.099
It's the Prosecco.

14:10.182 --> 14:11.600
Okay. Albie and I
are gonna go to our rooms.

14:11.684 --> 14:13.894
We'll come back for you
in a bit. You gonna be okay?

14:13.978 --> 14:15.396
-Uh...
-Great. (SIGHS)

14:17.523 --> 14:20.025
-(EXHALES)
-(SIGHS)

14:21.860 --> 14:24.780
-Why did we do this?
-(DOOR CLOSES)

14:24.863 --> 14:29.785
It's nice, Dad.
It's a nice thing to do.

14:29.868 --> 14:32.496
I got a migraine.
I'm gonna go lay down.

14:32.580 --> 14:36.667
Okay. Well, I'm probably
gonna head down to the pool.

14:36.750 --> 14:40.087
Um, and then what time
did you wanna meet up for...

14:41.547 --> 14:46.218
♪ (TENSE CHORAL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

14:48.387 --> 14:49.805
(SIGHS DEEPLY)

14:51.056 --> 14:53.350
(WATER BURBLING)

15:02.026 --> 15:05.613
VALENTINA: The most ancient art
is 14th century.

15:05.696 --> 15:08.032
-Oh, my God. Really?
-Yeah. (GASPS) Oh.

15:08.115 --> 15:10.784
-Your missing husband is here.
-(GASPS) Oh!

15:11.619 --> 15:13.162
-Oh, ho!
-TANYA: Hey.

15:13.787 --> 15:15.289
Hi!

15:15.372 --> 15:17.458
-How was the flight? Mm.
-TANYA: I missed you so much.

15:17.541 --> 15:18.834
(KISSES)

15:18.917 --> 15:22.838
Hey, uh, yeah, you know
I texted you a bunch of times.

15:22.921 --> 15:24.131
And you never texted me back.

15:24.214 --> 15:25.758
I know, I know. I'm sorry.

15:25.841 --> 15:27.801
We just had a flare-up
at work, it was--

15:27.885 --> 15:30.304
Shall I show
you your room, or...

15:30.387 --> 15:32.514
Oh. Yeah, definitely.

15:32.598 --> 15:34.266
What the hell
is she doing here?

15:34.350 --> 15:35.351
What?

15:35.434 --> 15:37.853
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

15:37.936 --> 15:40.731
(SIGHS) Yeah, uh, well, look.

15:41.440 --> 15:42.566
I'm traveling by myself--

15:42.650 --> 15:45.069
You bring your assistant
to a vacation with your husband?

15:45.152 --> 15:48.238
Anything you need,
I'll be there. Okay?

15:48.322 --> 15:49.990
Well, I just don't know
what the big deal is.

15:50.074 --> 15:51.533
I mean, I don't know
why you're so bothered.

15:51.617 --> 15:52.743
Because I said no!

15:54.870 --> 15:57.873
Because it's supposed
to be romantic.

15:57.956 --> 16:01.877
Because it's a vacation,
in Sicily, for us.

16:01.960 --> 16:03.045
I mean it's--

16:03.128 --> 16:04.755
(SIGHS SHARPLY) I mean,
it's not like she's, like,

16:04.838 --> 16:06.715
gonna be in our bed
and stuff, you know?

16:06.799 --> 16:09.468
-I mean, she has her own room.
-Tanya.

16:11.220 --> 16:12.513
Get rid of her.

16:12.596 --> 16:15.140
All right, I'll get rid of her.
I'll get rid of her. All right?

16:15.224 --> 16:16.725
-All right.
-Put her on a plane.

16:19.061 --> 16:21.772
TANYA: Hey. Um...

16:24.441 --> 16:26.068
You're gonna have to get lost.

16:27.736 --> 16:29.446
Okay. Yeah.

16:29.530 --> 16:32.825
So, what do you mean?
I'd see you in a week, then?

16:32.908 --> 16:35.160
No, no, no, no.
I want you to stay-- stay close,

16:35.244 --> 16:37.579
'cause I might need you.
But just lay low

16:37.663 --> 16:40.207
and-- and not come out
of your room. Okay?

16:40.290 --> 16:41.709
♪ (INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

16:41.792 --> 16:43.752
I gotta go. I gotta go!

16:46.797 --> 16:48.298
I did it. I did it.

16:49.842 --> 16:50.801
Oh. Hi, Portia.

16:50.884 --> 16:52.344
-Do you want a drink?
-(CHUCKLES SOFTLY)

16:52.428 --> 16:53.637
TANYA: I'm hungry.

16:53.721 --> 16:56.932
GREG HUNT: Well, we have these
little-- little things here.

16:57.015 --> 16:58.225
HARPER: I just think
it's like,

16:58.308 --> 17:00.519
you sold your company,
you got rich,

